the middle of Times Square,

13:24.449 --> 13:25.916
you can pretty much
do anything.

13:25.951 --> 13:27.451
I think it's time for you
to conquer this city.

13:27.486 --> 13:28.619
I don't know why
they call it Times Square.

13:28.653 --> 13:29.820
I don't see any clocks.

13:37.349 --> 13:40.251
Every art has its instrument.

13:40.286 --> 13:42.020
The violinist

13:42.054 --> 13:43.221
has his violin.

13:43.255 --> 13:45.090
The sculptor...

13:45.124 --> 13:47.158
has his stone.

13:47.193 --> 13:49.661
And the mime...

13:49.695 --> 13:51.096
has his body.

13:51.130 --> 13:53.765
Let us begin our work today
with the mime's

13:53.799 --> 13:56.668
most heartbreaking expression

13:56.702 --> 13:59.771
of his accursed, silent ennui:

13:59.805 --> 14:03.408
the pulling of
the invisible rope

14:03.442 --> 14:04.809
attached to something heavy.

14:14.920 --> 14:16.254
Psst.

14:16.288 --> 14:17.528
Psst.

14:19.358 --> 14:20.492
What are you doing here?

14:20.526 --> 14:22.160
This is a winter master class

14:22.194 --> 14:24.162
taught by Marcel Marceau's
illegitimate son Alain.

14:24.196 --> 14:25.463
You're-you're a freshman.

14:25.498 --> 14:27.532
I got special permission
from Madame Tibideaux.

14:27.566 --> 14:29.434
Turns out I'm in six
out of eight of your classes.

14:29.468 --> 14:30.535
How is that even possible?

14:30.569 --> 14:32.103
Stop talking!

14:32.138 --> 14:34.806
And now we will move on

14:34.840 --> 14:38.443
to the mime's most
tragic expression

14:38.477 --> 14:41.913
of the pointlessness
of man's existence.

14:41.947 --> 14:44.582
We are walking down the street,

14:44.617 --> 14:47.552
without a worry,
a care in the world,

14:47.586 --> 14:49.821
and suddenly we begin to notice

14:49.855 --> 14:51.523
that we are walking in place

14:51.557 --> 14:53.558
but we are not going anywhere.

14:56.262 --> 14:57.896
Have you asked Sam
to move out yet?

14:57.930 --> 14:59.230
We haven't had
a moment to ourselves.

14:59.265 --> 15:00.598
And now,

15:00.633 --> 15:02.967
we will stop to pick a flower.

15:04.336 --> 15:06.137
And in front of your eyes,

15:06.172 --> 15:07.806
the flower dies.

15:07.840 --> 15:09.407
Hey.

15:09.442 --> 15:11.876
Are you sure it's not me
who's crowding you?

15:11.911 --> 15:13.945
No, why would you say that?

15:13.979 --> 15:15.146
Good.

15:15.181 --> 15:17.182
I was really worried
I was suffocating you.

15:17.216 --> 15:19.684
So maybe after this,
we can get lunch?

15:19.719 --> 15:21.186
'Cause then we have Theatre
History class together

15:21.220 --> 15:22.854
and Auditioning for the
Camera class together...

15:22.888 --> 15:25.323
And now, you are trapped

15:25.357 --> 15:27.692
with the person next to you
in a box.

15:27.726 --> 15:29.527
At first, the box

15:29.562 --> 15:31.229
seems big enough
for the two of you.

15:31.263 --> 15:34.432
But then, the box
begins to shrink.

15:34.467 --> 15:35.900
The box where you live

15:35.935 --> 15:38.370
because that is all
a mime can afford.

15:38.404 --> 15:41.773
Getting smaller and smaller...

15:41.807 --> 15:45.577
and smaller... and smaller...

15:45.611 --> 15:47.212
and smaller.

15:49.991 --> 15:51.592
<i>It's that time.</i>

15:51.617 --> 15:53.952
<i>Time for change.</i>
<i>Reinvention.</i>

15:53.986 --> 15:57.288
<i>Rebirth.</i>
<i>That's what NYC is all about.</i>

15:57.323 --> 15:59.724
<i>Okay, maybe that's</i>
<i>a little dramatic,</i>

15:59.759 --> 16:01.025
<i>but don't kid yourself:</i>

16:01.060 --> 16:02.627
<i>getting a haircut</i>
<i>is a big deal.</i>

16:02.661 --> 16:04.295
<i>Normally, I wouldn't</i>
<i>take style advice</i>

16:04.330 --> 16:05.630
<i>from helmet-haired,</i>
<i>bow-tie-loving Blaine,</i>

16:05.664 --> 16:08.400
<i>but he really helped me</i>
<i>see the light.</i>

16:08.434 --> 16:10.435
<i>Or, in this case, the scissors.</i>

16:10.469 --> 16:12.670
<i>Yeah, I'll miss rocking</i>
<i>the bronytail, but you know,</i>

16:12.705 --> 16:14.139
<i>I need to jumpstart</i>
<i>this modeling operation,</i>

16:14.173 --> 16:15.473
<i>shake things up.</i>

16:17.243 --> 16:18.476
<i>Time for new headshots,</i>

16:18.511 --> 16:19.911
<i>new portfolio,</i>

16:19.945 --> 16:22.414
<i>new attitude.</i>

16:22.448 --> 16:25.316
<i>Because if there's</i>
<i>one thing I've learned,</i>

16:25.351 --> 16:26.885
<i>you can't just sit around</i>
<i>waiting for the good things</i>

16:26.919 --> 16:28.820
<i>in life to come to you.</i>

16:28.854 --> 16:31.556
<i>You need to kick down some</i>
<i>doors and make them happen.</i>

16:31.590 --> 16:34.059
<i>This is Sam Evans</i>
<i>like we've never seen before.</i>

16:35.428 --> 16:36.861
<i>Here I come, New York City.</i>

16:36.896 --> 16:38.363
I'm so close to owning this town

16:38.397 --> 16:40.365
I can practically taste it.

16:40.399 --> 16:42.634
Yeah, that computer cost
over 1,000 bucks.

16:42.668 --> 16:44.135
My-my credit card was in there,
my phone...

16:44.170 --> 16:45.336
Tell him that
he was on crutches.

16:45.371 --> 16:46.871
And...

16:46.906 --> 16:47.872
Yeah.

16:47.907 --> 16:49.474
Thanks so much for your help.

16:49.508 --> 16:51.142
That's it? Any leads?

16:51.177 --> 16:52.377
Blaine, do you have to

16:52.411 --> 16:53.611
use the SodaStream machine
right now?

16:53.646 --> 16:56.014
Artie's in a very fragile state.

16:56.048 --> 16:58.450
I'm sorry about him.
He just needs his bubbles.

16:58.484 --> 16:59.984
- Hey, guys.
- Hey, Rachel.

17:00.019 --> 17:01.920
Do you want a homemade

17:01.954 --> 17:03.154
sparkling, sugar-free soda?

17:03.189 --> 17:04.029
Oh, no thanks.

17:04.056 --> 17:05.022
The carbonation's

17:05.057 --> 17:06.357
bad for my vocal cords.

17:06.392 --> 17:07.858
But
you know what I will take?

17:07.893 --> 17:09.227
Just some, like, hot water

17:09.261 --> 17:10.361
with, like, a little lemon...

17:10.396 --> 17:11.596
Thank you so much.

17:11.630 --> 17:12.597
Rachel, you missed it.

17:12.631 --> 17:14.031
Artie was mugged in the subway,

17:14.066 --> 17:15.467
and now it's like an episode
of <i> SVU</i> over here.

17:15.501 --> 17:17.167
- What?
- Except for not at all.

17:17.203 --> 17:18.970
I wasn't touched, I was robbed.
Oh, my God.

17:19.003 --> 17:21.071
Are you okay?
No. Not really.

17:21.107 --> 17:22.807
I don't know what I'm gonna do
about replacing that computer,

17:22.842 --> 17:25.109
I need a new school ID,
and to be honest,

17:25.144 --> 17:27.011
I don't if I'm gonna feel safe
going in the subway anymore.

17:27.046 --> 17:29.481
I just felt so vulnerable
and I don't...

17:29.515 --> 17:30.648
I don't know... alone.

17:30.683 --> 17:32.717
Blaine, I'm gonna throw

17:32.752 --> 17:33.885
that machine out the window.

17:33.919 --> 17:35.186
I am so sorry,

17:35.221 --> 17:36.788
but I know exactly
how you feel, okay?

17:36.822 --> 17:38.022
When I first moved to New York,

17:38.057 --> 17:39.324
I gave this homeless
person ten dollars

17:39.358 --> 17:40.558
when I just meant
to give him one,

17:40.593 --> 17:42.060
and then when I
asked for it back,

17:42.094 --> 17:43.895
everyone hissed and
they booed at me,

17:43.929 --> 17:45.363
and I felt so violated
and vulnerable.

17:45.398 --> 17:47.499
Oh, wait.
So you were out nine dollars?

17:47.533 --> 17:49.367
But look, the next day

17:49.402 --> 17:51.069
I just got right
back on that subway,

17:51.103 --> 17:52.537
because overcoming
experiences like that

17:52.571 --> 17:54.506
is what makes you
a real New Yorker.

17:54.540 --> 17:56.241
Your beverage, milady.

17:56.275 --> 17:57.976
Oh, are those Meyer lemons?

17:58.911 --> 18:00.011
No, I can't have that.

18:00.046 --> 18:01.212
You know what, Rachel?

18:01.247 --> 18:02.714
Don't lecture me

18:02.748 --> 18:04.015
about being a real New Yorker

18:04.050 --> 18:06.184
with your lemon water
and your chauffeured limousine.

18:06.218 --> 18:08.053
You're not even a
real person anymore.

18:08.087 --> 18:09.854
Now, if you'll just excuse me,

18:09.889 --> 18:12.249
I have to go figure out how
to put my life back together.

18:13.459 --> 18:15.460
It's a town car,
not a limousine.

18:17.596 --> 18:18.463
It's a town car.

18:18.497 --> 18:19.931
Okay?

18:19.965 --> 18:22.067
A town car.

