have that sexy,

24:08.741 --> 24:11.176
round, onion booty
that they've always dreamed of.

24:11.210 --> 24:13.478
I didn't even know
there was a market for that,

24:13.512 --> 24:15.313
but that is great.

24:15.347 --> 24:17.348
And I got you a free pair!

24:17.383 --> 24:21.219
Oh, thank you. I, um,
can't wait to show Kurt.

24:21.253 --> 24:23.721
The good news keeps
coming, my brother. I...

24:23.756 --> 24:25.824
am moving out.

24:25.858 --> 24:27.625
Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa.
You're-you're moving?

24:27.660 --> 24:29.660
Where you going to?
Well, the agency's

24:29.662 --> 24:31.062
putting me up in an apartment
with a bunch of other models.

24:31.096 --> 24:33.331
I'm stoked.
My own place, sort of,

24:33.365 --> 24:34.766
and you know, I'm not gonna be

24:34.800 --> 24:36.401
taking up any more room
on the couch.

24:36.435 --> 24:39.537
Well, you're gonna visit us,
right?

24:39.572 --> 24:41.739
Um, yeah, if I have time,
you know.

24:41.774 --> 24:45.410
But I-I-I might be traveling
to Paris and Milan

24:45.444 --> 24:47.612
every week. Who knows?

24:48.714 --> 24:50.048
I'm gonna pack everything up.

24:50.082 --> 24:51.549
Yeah.

24:55.321 --> 24:58.356
Hey! Oh, did you hear
Sam just got a job?

24:58.390 --> 25:00.091
What are you doing?

25:00.126 --> 25:01.366
Uh, this is, uh, something

25:01.393 --> 25:03.328
I thought would make
a really great office area.

25:03.362 --> 25:05.730
Back away from the lamp, okay?!
When someone enters

25:05.765 --> 25:08.333
their sanctuary, they don't want
their eyes immediately drawn

25:08.367 --> 25:09.601
to a hideous workspace!

25:09.635 --> 25:10.735
I'm not done yet.

25:10.770 --> 25:12.804
This isn't McKinley.
You can't just barge in here

25:12.838 --> 25:14.105
and do whatever you want,
whenever you want, all right?

25:14.140 --> 25:15.540
You could've at least
consulted me

25:15.574 --> 25:18.243
before making design decisions
in my home!

25:18.277 --> 25:20.645
I thought that this was supposed
to be <i> our</i> home, Kurt.

25:20.679 --> 25:24.616
And believe it or not, not
every single design decision

25:24.650 --> 25:26.751
you make is brilliant.
This whole privacy-

25:26.786 --> 25:29.487
curtains-between-the-bedrooms
thing is stupid. Come on.

25:29.522 --> 25:31.489
We can hear every single noise
our roomies make at night,

25:31.524 --> 25:32.724
and God knows
what they hear from us.

25:32.758 --> 25:34.259
You know what?
Elliott was right,

25:34.293 --> 25:35.560
we're losing our boundaries.

25:35.594 --> 25:37.061
I'm sorry, Elliott?
What-What does Elliot have

25:37.096 --> 25:38.263
to do with any of this?

25:38.297 --> 25:39.230
We were talking.

25:39.265 --> 25:40.532
I bet you were talking.

25:40.566 --> 25:41.432
He's my friend.

25:41.467 --> 25:42.901
I bet he's your friend.

25:42.935 --> 25:44.602
Calm down, psycho, all right?

25:44.637 --> 25:46.771
And stop being so pouty
and weird. It's annoying.

25:46.806 --> 25:49.507
All right, let's just be
adults and put everything back

25:49.542 --> 25:50.942
where it's supposed to go.

25:50.976 --> 25:53.378
Okay, I got an idea.
Why don't you put it back

25:53.412 --> 25:55.413
where it's supposed to go
because it's your apartment!

25:55.448 --> 25:57.615
Fine! I will!

26:07.760 --> 26:09.727
Hey, move it, kid!

26:23.098 --> 26:24.778
Who is it?

26:24.803 --> 26:26.737
It's Blaine.

26:26.771 --> 26:28.272
Hey, I...

26:30.742 --> 26:31.909
Are you okay?

26:31.943 --> 26:32.943
Oh...

26:32.977 --> 26:34.445
Oh, God, you're not trying

26:34.479 --> 26:35.846
to move in here, are you?

26:35.880 --> 26:38.282
No, I'm not. We need to talk.
I don't have

26:38.316 --> 26:39.917
your number and
I don't have your e-mail

26:39.951 --> 26:42.019
and we're not friend on Facebook
because I made it a point

26:42.053 --> 26:44.722
of waiting for you to friend me,
which you never did, by the way.

26:44.756 --> 26:47.057
So here I am
face-to-face.

26:47.092 --> 26:49.093
I just want to hear you
admit it.

26:49.127 --> 26:50.828
Admit what?

26:50.862 --> 26:54.565
That you're trying to steal Kurt
away from me, Starchild Gilbert!

26:54.599 --> 26:56.166
What?!
What are you talking about?

26:56.201 --> 27:00.437
Please, I was on to you
the second I saw

27:00.472 --> 27:02.512
that weird cinnamon roll selfie
you took months ago.

27:02.540 --> 27:03.941
You guys posted that.
Remember that?

27:03.975 --> 27:05.976
I get to New York
and all of a sudden

27:06.010 --> 27:09.079
it's "Elliott thinks this"
and "Elliott thinks that"

27:09.114 --> 27:11.115
and "Elliott's hair
is so full and thick

27:11.149 --> 27:13.250
that he doesn't have
to rely on hair gel."

27:13.284 --> 27:17.921
Well, I may not be a cool
steampunk, glitter-rock vampire

27:17.956 --> 27:20.457
with, like, tats and guyliner,

27:20.492 --> 27:23.427
but you know what?
I love Kurt. I love him!

27:23.461 --> 27:27.531
He's my fiancé, not
yours, so back off!

27:27.565 --> 27:30.467
Okay, are... are you done?

27:32.604 --> 27:33.971
Take this.

27:34.005 --> 27:36.407
- What? - Yeah, it's, uh,
it's like a body pillow.

27:36.441 --> 27:37.808
It think it's
gonna calm you down.

27:37.842 --> 27:39.176
Take a seat.

27:42.380 --> 27:45.082
Look, Blaine,
I'm not after Kurt.

27:45.116 --> 27:47.851
We're just friends. Don't get
me wrong, I mean, he's a,

27:47.886 --> 27:50.654
he's a cute guy, but I don't
think of him that way.

27:50.688 --> 27:54.425
And even if I did,
Kurt loves you.

27:54.459 --> 27:57.928
I mean, he-he doesn't
shut up about you, actually.

27:57.962 --> 27:59.196
Like, ever.

28:00.765 --> 28:03.367
I'm sorry. I don't know
what's going on with me.

28:03.401 --> 28:08.205
It's just, we've been apart
for so long,

28:08.239 --> 28:13.210
and now that I'm finally here,
I just want to catch up to him,

28:13.244 --> 28:14.945
I just want to make it real.

28:14.979 --> 28:16.280
And the more I try...

28:16.314 --> 28:17.481
The more it pushes him away?

28:18.683 --> 28:21.685
Well, maybe you should
stop trying.

28:23.054 --> 28:27.057
I mean, look, New York
is a really crowded place,

28:27.092 --> 28:29.572
and people need a little more
room to breathe here than usual.

28:29.594 --> 28:31.695
You're right.

28:34.032 --> 28:38.402
I guess I always think
of boundaries as walls

28:38.436 --> 28:42.106
instead of places to grow in.

28:43.575 --> 28:45.375
I'm so sorry. I-I should go.

28:45.410 --> 28:46.777
Hey, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

28:46.811 --> 28:48.212
You just got here.

28:48.246 --> 28:50.147
You want to just hang out
for a minute?

28:50.181 --> 28:51.315
Um...

28:51.349 --> 28:53.584
I mean, you've obviously
come to jam.

28:53.618 --> 28:55.052
Um... you gave me this.

28:55.086 --> 28:56.320
"Glitter-rock vampire," huh?

28:56.354 --> 28:57.514
I didn't mean that.
I'm sorry.

28:57.522 --> 29:00.357
I like that.
I-I... I can work with that.

29:00.392 --> 29:01.558
Okay, okay, all right.

29:01.593 --> 29:03.227
Come on.
Give me some blues.

29:03.261 --> 29:04.762
Give me some Southern...
Come on.

29:04.796 --> 29:06.463
Uh... um... gli...

29:06.498 --> 29:09.466
♪ Glitter-rock vampire ♪

29:09.501 --> 29:12.536
♪ Gonna bite ya ♪

29:12.570 --> 29:14.271
♪ Gonna bite ya ♪

29:14.305 --> 29:16.273
♪ Gonna bite ya. ♪

29:22.247 --> 29:23.881
Hey.

29:23.915 --> 29:25.082
I got your text.

29:25.116 --> 29:28.519
Why did her Royal Highness
summon a commoner like me?

29:28.553 --> 29:31.121
Okay, that was a little rude,
but I know I had it coming.

29:31.156 --> 29:33.724
Look, I had an epiphany, and you
were right, okay? About everything.

29:33.758 --> 29:35.692
I don't want to be
sheltered from the world,

29:35.727 --> 29:37.661
I want to live in it.
So let's go.

29:37.695 --> 29:40.064
I have rehearsal and you have class.
Let's take the subway.

29:40.098 --> 29:41.632
No, I can't.
No, together.

29:41.666 --> 29:43.167
Look, I know that you're
a little shaken up

29:43.201 --> 29:45.369
about what happened, but trust
me, but I took Krav Maga

29:45.403 --> 29:47.483
as a child at the JCC,
and I can protect you.

29:53.144 --> 29:55.112
So what about the limo?

29:55.146 --> 29:56.513
Town car. And
I gave it up.

29:56.548 --> 29:58.649
I told my producers I'd
be in a much better place

29:58.683 --> 30:00.617
if I rode the subway
with my friend every day.

30:00.652 --> 30:02.319
Every day? Well,
if you'll have me.

30:02.353 --> 30:03.587
Look, I will make you a deal.

30:03.621 --> 30:05.322
I'll ride the subway
with you and make sure

30:05.356 --> 30:06.824
that you don't get mugged again

30:06.858 --> 30:09.526
if you give me a tongue-
lashing if I lose my way.

30:09.561 --> 30:11.061
I can do that.

30:11.096 --> 30:13.063
I'm really happy that
you're in New York.

30:13.098 --> 30:15.599
The city is a much less
scarier place with a friend.

30:15.633 --> 30:18.235
And I'm really happy you dragged
me back down here, because...

30:18.269 --> 30:19.737
I really do love it.

30:24.309 --> 30:26.677
♪ You wander around ♪

30:26.711 --> 30:30.247
♪ On your own little cloud ♪

30:30.281 --> 30:33.684
♪ When you don't see the why ♪

30:33.718 --> 30:37.654
♪ Or the wherefore ♪

30:37.689 --> 30:40.724
♪ Ooh, you walk out on me ♪

30:40.759 --> 30:44.528
♪ When we both disagree ♪

30:44.562 --> 30:47.231
♪ 'Cause to reason is ♪

30:47.265 --> 30:52.069
♪ Not what you care for ♪

30:52.103 --> 30:55.406
♪ Good-bye means nothing ♪

30:55.440 --> 30:59.343
♪ When it's all for show ♪

30:59.377 --> 31:02.246
♪ So why pretend ♪

31:02.280 --> 31:06.850
♪ You've somewhere else to go ♪

31:06.885 --> 31:10.621
♪ Don't sleep
in the subway, darlin' ♪

31:10.655 --> 31:14.124
♪ Don't stand
in the pouring rain ♪

31:14.159 --> 31:17.594
♪ Don't sleep
in the subway, darlin' ♪

31:17.629 --> 31:19.063
♪ The night is long ♪

31:19.097 --> 31:22.166
♪ Forget your foolish pride,
nothing's wrong ♪

31:22.200 --> 31:25.769
♪ Now you're beside me again ♪

31:27.572 --> 31:29.039
♪ Oh ♪

31:29.074 --> 31:32.543
♪ Don't sleep in the subway ♪
♪ Darlin' ♪

31:32.577 --> 31:35.913
♪ Don't stand
in the pouring rain ♪

31:35.947 --> 31:39.116
♪ Don't sleep
in the subway, darlin' ♪

31:39.150 --> 31:40.784
♪ The night is long ♪

31:40.819 --> 31:44.555
♪ Forget your foolish pride,
nothing's wrong ♪

31:44.589 --> 31:49.393
♪ And you're beside me again. ♪

31:56.458 --> 31:58.335
I think there's like a dozen models
living in here,

31:58.356 --> 32:00.836
but people take off for weeks
at a time on photo shoots,

32:00.861 --> 32:02.061
so it never gets too crowded.

32:02.095 --> 32:03.229
The rooms are kind of small.

32:03.263 --> 32:04.497
Oh, that's okay;
I've been homeless.

32:04.531 --> 32:05.598
That's cool, man.

32:05.632 --> 32:06.899
I envy your realness.

32:06.933 --> 32:08.567
Listen, I got to do this
paid webcam thing in my room,

32:08.602 --> 32:09.902
but if you have any
other questions,

32:09.936 --> 32:11.070
just ask your roommate Sam.

32:11.104 --> 32:13.305
Wait, my roommate's name is Sam?

32:13.340 --> 32:14.907
Okay, this couldn't get
any cooler.

32:14.941 --> 32:16.442
- I'm sorry.
- Hi.

32:16.476 --> 32:17.877
I'm Sam.

32:19.946 --> 32:21.080
What?

32:24.951 --> 32:26.986
- Hey.
- Hi.

32:27.020 --> 32:28.954
So you went to see Elliot.

32:30.991 --> 32:33.125
I did.

32:33.159 --> 32:34.493
He's a good guy.

32:34.528 --> 32:36.295
He's a good friend to you.

32:36.329 --> 32:37.530
He's one of
the only real friends

32:37.564 --> 32:38.724
I've made since I came here.

32:40.166 --> 32:43.102
He texted me as soon
as you left his apartment.

32:43.136 --> 32:44.470
Six hours ago.

32:45.502 --> 32:47.382
So I guess
I've just been wondering

32:47.407 --> 32:48.507
where you've been.

32:49.509 --> 32:51.677
Well, I, um...

32:51.711 --> 32:54.380
I actually took a water taxi

32:54.414 --> 32:56.749
to the Statue of Liberty.

32:56.783 --> 32:58.784
Just needed some space
so I could think.

32:58.818 --> 33:01.787
I went to the High Line
to do the same.

33:03.156 --> 33:05.024
Well, then can I go first?

33:19.606 --> 33:21.874
I think I should move out.

33:21.908 --> 33:24.176
I'm not sure that's what I want.

33:24.211 --> 33:26.512
Me neither, but I think...

33:26.546 --> 33:28.547
we need to take a step back

33:28.582 --> 33:32.017
for a second together and...

33:32.052 --> 33:35.888
just look at the situation

33:35.922 --> 33:39.491
honestly.

33:39.526 --> 33:41.527
It's not working out.

33:43.763 --> 33:46.065
After graduation, I just...

33:46.099 --> 33:48.267
moved in and we didn't have
a conversation about it.

33:48.301 --> 33:50.336
We never weighed
the pros and cons.

33:50.370 --> 33:52.705
We never really discussed

33:52.739 --> 33:56.075
if this was
the absolute best thing

33:56.109 --> 33:57.943
for our relationship.

33:57.978 --> 34:00.079
We just wanted to be us.
Together.

34:00.113 --> 34:01.914
And-and we are together.

34:01.948 --> 34:03.082
We are so together,

34:03.116 --> 34:06.385
but I just think that maybe...

34:06.419 --> 34:08.020
living together

34:08.054 --> 34:11.489
in less
than ideal circumstances...

34:11.525 --> 34:13.359
Maybe we don't need
that pressure right now.

34:13.393 --> 34:16.094
I mean, it's such
a scary decision to make.

34:16.129 --> 34:17.862
I-I just, I feel like I-I...

34:17.898 --> 34:19.031
I know, I know.

34:19.065 --> 34:20.331
It is scary,

34:20.367 --> 34:23.068
but I think it's
a little less scary if...

34:23.103 --> 34:25.004
we make the decision together.

34:25.038 --> 34:26.405
We can't go backwards.

34:26.438 --> 34:28.440
We're not going backwards.

34:28.475 --> 34:30.775
I think we're...

34:30.810 --> 34:32.378
being smart.

34:32.411 --> 34:37.049
By protecting something
that is very precious to me.

34:38.051 --> 34:40.018
You know that, right?

34:40.053 --> 34:42.353
Of course I know that.
Of course.

34:42.389 --> 34:44.389
Always. I know.

34:49.262 --> 34:51.163
And no matter who we become,

34:51.197 --> 34:53.098
even if we do need alone time...

34:53.132 --> 34:54.800
which is completely valid...

34:54.835 --> 34:56.715
we'll always belong
to each other.

35:06.150 --> 35:08.190
And even though
this-this wasn't a fight,

35:08.215 --> 35:11.183
this was just, you know,
a grown-up, adult conversation...

35:11.218 --> 35:14.453
you know, we are now

35:14.487 --> 35:16.555
going to have
the hottest makeup sex ever.

35:16.590 --> 35:18.424
Okay.

35:18.458 --> 35:21.527
It never hurts
to sing when you're going on a casting.

35:21.561 --> 35:23.762
You do the best impressions!

35:23.797 --> 35:25.297
That's so Kathy Ireland.

35:25.332 --> 35:26.632
Huh.

35:26.666 --> 35:28.167
Okay, now do Gisele.

35:28.201 --> 35:30.336
No, I should probably, uh... I
should probably get some sleep.

35:30.370 --> 35:32.505
I-I got a big follow-up photo
shoot with, uh, Bubble tomorrow.

35:32.539 --> 35:34.440
The wonderbutt undies?

35:34.474 --> 35:35.741
Oh, my God, Sam!

35:35.775 --> 35:37.443
Congratulations. That's great.

35:37.477 --> 35:39.078
- Thanks.
- Okay, well, look,

35:39.112 --> 35:40.346
use these.

35:40.380 --> 35:41.747
I swear by it.

35:41.781 --> 35:43.682
It keeps your body
from retaining <i> any</i> water.

35:43.717 --> 35:45.985
I have Adderall if you want.

35:46.019 --> 35:48.454
Oh, if you have trouble
sleeping, Marla has Ambien.

35:48.488 --> 35:50.322
I prefer Lunesta.

35:50.357 --> 35:52.091
My schedule's been
so cray lately.

35:52.125 --> 35:54.260
But don't take
whatever Gavin has.

35:54.294 --> 35:56.262
He says it's clenbuterol,

35:56.296 --> 35:58.430
but I swear
it's like pig tranquilizers.

35:58.465 --> 36:00.199
Sorry. I got to go.

36:01.635 --> 36:03.369
You don't have anything
for anxiety, do you?

36:03.403 --> 36:06.372
I don't, uh... don't think
I can stay here.

36:06.406 --> 36:08.140
I hate everything.

36:08.174 --> 36:09.775
Sam?

36:11.077 --> 36:12.611
Oh, my God, you guys

36:12.646 --> 36:14.947
are not gonna believe what
happened to me and Artie today.

36:14.981 --> 36:16.515
- Sam? - Sam, come here.
Listen to this.

36:16.550 --> 36:17.710
I know this is going to sound

36:17.717 --> 36:18.951
like one of those crazy
New York stories,

36:18.985 --> 36:20.219
and I wouldn't believe it myself

36:20.253 --> 36:21.820
if it hadn't just happened,
but I swear...

36:21.855 --> 36:23.489
- Just tell us.
- Okay, right.

36:23.523 --> 36:24.690
So, Rachel and I
were riding the L-Train.

36:24.724 --> 36:26.992
Take a little nap right now.

36:27.027 --> 36:28.928
- Oh, my God, it's him.
- Who?

36:28.962 --> 36:30.162
The guy who mugged me.

36:30.197 --> 36:31.463
Oh, no.

36:31.498 --> 36:32.898
Yeah.

36:32.933 --> 36:33.866
Shut up.

36:33.900 --> 36:35.234
Okay, so then, we see this guy,

36:35.268 --> 36:36.569
and he's, like, inching
towards this super sweet,

36:36.603 --> 36:37.903
elegant, elderly-looking
lady, who'd obviously,

36:37.938 --> 36:39.238
like, had a little
bit of work done,

36:39.272 --> 36:41.240
but it was very tasteful. Just,
like, right around her eyes.

36:41.274 --> 36:43.242
And this guy was eyeing
her gorgeous Hermès Birkin bag.

36:43.276 --> 36:44.310
And then...

36:44.344 --> 36:46.011
- It's pepper spray.
- Let me do it.

36:46.046 --> 36:48.047
Go! Be careful.

36:51.401 --> 36:53.562
I cut him off and sprayed him
right in the eye.

36:53.587 --> 36:55.421
God, I felt so vindicated.

36:55.455 --> 36:56.422
It was amazing.

36:56.456 --> 36:57.723
And when we got off the subway,

36:57.757 --> 36:59.358
we found out that this
guy got arrested, and

36:59.392 --> 37:00.912
it turns out that
he's, like, a mugger,

37:00.927 --> 37:03.195
slash, hoarder, so all this
stuff was just at his apartment.

37:03.230 --> 37:04.763
Yeah, and the cops
found my laptop!

37:04.798 --> 37:05.998
- It's amazing.
- Great.

37:06.032 --> 37:07.199
You're like a real
life Professor X.

37:07.234 --> 37:08.767
Yeah.
It's so great.

37:08.802 --> 37:09.501
That was pretty amazing.

37:09.536 --> 37:10.769
Well, Kurt and I

37:10.804 --> 37:12.371
have had a bit of a big day
ourselves, actually.

37:12.405 --> 37:13.973
Well, it wasn't
as dramatic as that.

37:14.007 --> 37:16.108
Well, it-it was...
it was pretty dramatic.

37:16.142 --> 37:18.777
Um, we decided
that I'm going to move out.

37:18.812 --> 37:20.045
- Shut up!
- Really?

37:20.080 --> 37:21.213
Don't worry.
We're not breaking up.

37:21.248 --> 37:22.548
Oh, no, no, no, far from it.

37:22.582 --> 37:23.883
We actually think this is gonna
strengthen our relationship.

37:23.917 --> 37:25.217
Yeah, I said
he needs to discover the city

37:25.252 --> 37:26.385
the same way I got to.

37:26.419 --> 37:27.553
You know,
find his favorite neighborhood,

37:27.587 --> 37:28.721
find his favorite pizza place.

37:28.755 --> 37:30.556
You know, have
some time and space

37:30.590 --> 37:32.758
to explore and grow
and find out who he is here.

37:32.792 --> 37:34.193
And to that
end, my first thought

37:34.227 --> 37:36.495
is that I'm a guy
that wouldn't mind crashing

37:36.530 --> 37:38.397
on Sam's couch
in his new apartment.

37:38.431 --> 37:41.667
I actually... I actually don't
have a new apartment anymore.

37:41.701 --> 37:43.135
Um, I moved out.

37:43.169 --> 37:45.738
That place... it
wasn't it for me.

37:45.772 --> 37:48.252
I'm not saying I'm giving up
my dream of being a model.

37:48.275 --> 37:49.074
I still want that

37:49.109 --> 37:50.242
more than ever.

37:50.277 --> 37:51.644
I just... I want to
do it the right way

37:51.678 --> 37:53.879
with, you know, no puking,
